        "title": "Docker Compose getting exception",
        "body": "<p>I have a spring boot application which i have deployed on docker container, everything is working fine, but i want to deploy and run the application in docker container with docker compose.<\/p>\n\n<p>This is my DockerFile<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>FROM java:8\nVOLUME /tmp\nCOPY /target/order-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar order.jar\nENTRYPOINT [\"java\",\"-Djava.security.egd=file:/dev/./urandom\",\"-jar\",\"/order.jar\"]\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Step 1 :- Created jar with mvn clean package  <br/>\nStep 2 :- docker build -t order  <br/>\nStep 3 :- docker run -it -d -p 8080:8080   <br/><\/p>\n\n<p>Here everything work's fine  <br/><\/p>\n\n<p>But if i don't execute the step 1 and want's to deploy the the application in container with docker-compose. <\/p>\n\n<p>While trying to execute docker-compose up i am getting exception /target/order-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar not found<\/p>\n\n<p>So how to execute the <b>mvn package command<\/b> in docker-compose ?<\/p>\n\n<p>Is their any other way's to acheive this ?<\/p>\n\n<p>This is my docker-compose.yml<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>version: '3'\nservices:\n  order:\n    restart: always\n    build: ./order\n    working_dir: /order\n    volumes:\n      - /tmp:/logs\n    expose:\n      - \"8080\"\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
